## File structure:
.
├── doc.pdf
├── readme
├── result_5.pdf
├── result_5.v
├── run.sh
└── work
    ├── bin
    │   └── logicLoopChecker                       # The executable file
    ├── build.sh                                   # The build script
    ├── setUpSystemFunc_verisim.cpp                # The enter of the program
    ├── src
    │   ├── checker.py                             # Our script to check the result
    │   └── logicLoopChecker                       # Our source code
    ├── sv_vpi_user.h
    ├── systf.tab
    └── vpi_user.h


## Run:
1. ${SCRIPT_DIR}/run.sh ${CASE_DIR}/case.v # The results will be generated in pwd

## Note:
We use `std::system` in `setUpSystemFunc_verisim.cpp` to. If you want to build it:
1. cd work/
2. ./build.sh # This will compile the source code and copy the executable file to ~/submission/work/bin/